Ac'r II. SCENE VI. Simo endeavours to discover from Davus whether Pamphilus still entertains any affection for Glycerium. Davus evades the question, and attributes the apparent sadness of Pamphilus to mor- tification at his father’s niggardly prepara- tions for the wedding. At the same time Simo suspects that some trick is in the wind, and feels sure that whatever it is Davus is at the bottom of it.
